Subject: [2/7] slayzone: chrome:// scheme handler factory + empty
 slayzone-shell (Phase 2.2)

Replaces the throwaway Phase-1 chrome://hello/ registration with a
generic factory that every Phase 5+ region lands its WebUIConfig in.
The patch also ships the first real SlayZone WebUI: chrome://slayzone-shell/
as an empty placeholder body. Phase 2.5 points the NTP at it; Phase 7.1
replaces the inline HTML with the real Shell region.

- chrome/browser/ui/webui/slayzone/slayzone_webui_registry.{h,cc}:
  new. Exposes RegisterSlayzoneWebUIConfigs(WebUIConfigMap&) as the
  single entrypoint called from RegisterChromeWebUIConfigs(). Hosts
  ShellUI + ShellUIConfig inline as the first tenant; future regions
  land their own *_ui.cc files and get added to the registry here.
  Serves via SetRequestFilter so Phase 2 stays decoupled from the
  grit pipeline (Phase 4 migrates every region to generated
  resources).
- chrome/browser/ui/BUILD.gn: registry sources wired into the `ui`
  target next to the other webui/ entries.
- chrome/browser/ui/webui/chrome_web_ui_configs.cc: include +
  single RegisterSlayzoneWebUIConfigs(map) call at end.
- chrome/common/webui_url_constants.{h,cc}: kChromeUISlayzoneShellHost
  ("slayzone-shell") + URL constant; host added to ChromeURLHosts so
  it shows up in chrome://chrome-urls next to the built-ins.
